<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: WHO'S THAT GIRL? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By David J. Fox 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
You see her limbs, her thighs, her hands -- and one shot of her from behind, 
climbing from a swimming pool unclothed. But in "Welcome Home, Roxy 
Carmichael," while the camera tantalizes, it never reveals the face of the 
title character. 
</P>
<P>
The movie is set in Roxy's hometown, where residents await her homecoming. 
Wynona Ryder and Jeff Daniels star. 
</P>
<P>
Roxy's voluptuous body actually belongs to Ava Fabian, 28, former Playboy 
Playmate (August, 1986), who hails from Brewster, N.Y., and now lives in 
Hollywood. She has appeared -- face and all -- in the feature film "Dragnet," 
the upcoming "Auntie Lee's Meat Pies" and TV's "Married With Children." 
</P>
<P>
"It was one of the easiest parts I've ever had," Fabian says of her role as 
Roxy. "There was no dialogue." David J. Fox 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Ava Fabian . . . here you see her face, there you don't. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
