<HEADLINE>
<P>
OBSERVATIONS ON 'THE CIVIL WAR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As I watch the remarkable account of the American Civil War on PBS, I am 
reminded that during that war most of the combatants and civilians forgot, over 
time, what the war was all about: to preserve the Union. 
</P>
<P>
I am reminded that today in the situation we face with Iraq many of us have 
forgotten already why the Union is in the Middle East. 
</P>
<P>
It is not oil that introduced our armies to Saudi soil, but the right of 
self-determination of peoples. Now we talk only about oil prices, oil supplies, 
oil prices. 
</P>
<P>
If we are to enter into a conflict that may terminate the lives of innocent 
Americans and others, then let it be for the right reason -- the primary reason 
Americans have put their lives on the line throughout our history -- for the 
right of liberty. 
</P>
<P>
L.M. LARRY EDMONDS 
</P>
<P>
Redondo Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
