<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUBERNATORIAL CANDIDATES DEBATE ISSUES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The drug-war plans of Wilson and Feinstein show the same old failed approach. 
</P>
<P>
They would both spend money to provide more drug treatment for their children 
and more prisons for minority children. 
</P>
<P>
When any budget is divided the way they did, the upper classes will get 
treatment, while the lower classes will get jail. They need to recognize that 
jail is not a solution for drug abuse. 
</P>
<P>
CLIFFORD A. SCHAFFER 
</P>
<P>
Canyon Country 
</P>
</TEXT>
