By KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wish You Were Here (CBS Friday at 9 p.m.) introduces us to teen-age actress 
Emily Lloyd, whose performance as a cheeky 15-year-old in a staid English town 
is one of those extraordinary fusions of actress and role that defy you to pry 
them apart. 
</P>
<P>
The Saturday night lineup of oldies but goodies should tempt anyone to stay 
home: King's Row (KTLA at 8 p.m.) -- the former president's best; Hud (KCOP at 
8 p.m.), Laura (KCET at 9 p.m.) and, best of all, Detour (KCETat 10:30 p.m.), 
Edgar Ulmer's fast and furious film noir classic. 
</P>
