<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHITE HOUSE AIDES BUNGLING TAX ISSUE, LYN NOFZIGER SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former White House political adviser Lyn Nofziger said Friday his successors 
serving President Bush have created a "public relations disaster" on the budget 
debate over the tax issue. 
</P>
<P>
"I think that what we're seeing is a need for consistency, and that's what we 
haven't seen here in the last week and it's too bad because the President is 
really better than that," said Nofziger. 
</P>
<P>
Nofziger, who was a member of President Reagan's inner circle, was interviewed 
on the "Fox Morning News" about the White House's apparent changes of position 
during the budget debate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
