<HEADLINE>
<P>
ONLY WEALTHY CAN AFFORD THE FARES AT JOHN WAYNE AIRPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Now that all the hoopla for the Orange County airport has died down, let's stop 
and realize that this airport is basically just for the rich. 
</P>
<P>
Recently, four friends and I decided to spend a weekend in Scottsdale. 
</P>
<P>
Flights from Ontario, Long Beach and Los Angeles airports averaged between $48 
and $68. The same flight out of Orange County was $220. Moreover, the cost of 
overnight parking is ridiculously high. 
</P>
<P>
Needless to say, my friends and I will be driving past John Wayne Airport on 
our way to Los Angeles International Airport (and adding to the rush-hour 
gridlock) because the air fares are too high for us middle-class peons. 
</P>
<P>
Another thought. All the executives in my office demand that we secretaries 
book their flights out of John Wayne Airport when they are traveling for 
company business. 
</P>
<P>
However, when these same executives are planning their vacations and thus every 
nickel is their own, they make sure their flights are out of any airport but 
Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
NINA KING 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
