<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NORTHRIDGE BACKFIELD LEADS WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tailback Albert Fann rushed for 136 yards and three touchdowns and fullback 
Anthony Nicholson also gained 136 yards Saturday to lead Cal State Northridge 
to a 34-24 victory over Southern Utah in a Western Football Conference game at 
Cedar City, Utah. 
</P>
<P>
Fann, a senior, had 38 carries and scored on two one-yard runs and a four-yard 
run. 
</P>
<P>
Nicholson, a junior, had 19 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge, 5-1 overall and 2-0 in the conference, moved into first place in 
the conference, half a game ahead of Southern Utah (4-3, 2-1) and a game ahead 
of Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, a 20-17 loser to Cal State Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors, ranked 15th in Division II, were outgained, 440 total yards to 
385, but forced six turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
Included was an interception and 33-yard return for a touchdown by nose tackle 
Alo Sila with just over 12 minutes left that put the Matadors in the lead to 
stay, 24-17. 
</P>
<P>
Abo Velasco kicked field goals of 34 and 50 yards for Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Southern Utah scored on a 19-yard run by Steve Hutchings, a two-yard run by 
Scott Firestone, a 33-yard pass play from Brad Matthews to Dan Silcox and a 
28-yard field goal by Rick Cadwallader. 
</P>
<P>
La Verne 28, Whittier 14 -- Chris Nance rushed for 116 yards in 17 carries and 
scored a touchdown as the Leopards (1-4, 1-3) defeated the Poets (0-5, 0-4) in 
a Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference game at Whittier. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 14, Claremont-Mudd 7 -- Quarterback Cassidy O'Sullivan and 
receiver Tom Leogrande connected on a 19-yard touchdown pass play with 1:12 
left to give the Kingsmen (1-5) the victory over the Stags (1-4) in a 
nonconference game at Claremont. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran freshman Jay Weber gained 126 yards in 32 carries. 
</P>
