PISTONS BEAT CLIPPERS AGAIN AS THOMAS TAKES OVER, 118-111 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Isiah Thomas' 14 third-quarter points helped the defending NBA champion Detroit 
Pistons rally for a 118-111 exhibition win over the Clippers on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
The Pistons are 2-0 in the exhibition season, both wins coming against the 
Clippers. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas led the Pistons with 19 points and center James Edwards added 18. The 
Clippers' Ken Norman led all scorers with 26 points. 
</P>
<P>
The Pistons trailed, 58-57, at halftime and led, 81-80, with 1:30 left in the 
third quarter when Thomas scored five consecutive points to stretch the 
Pistons' lead to six. Detroit led by as many as 12 during the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
The Clippers trailed, 49-39, with 6:20 left in the second quarter, but battled 
back behind Norman's 14 second-quarter points to go ahead before halftime. 
