<HEADLINE>
<P>
INFANT AND GIRL, 5, KILLED IN CAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 7-week-old infant and a 5-year-old girl were killed Saturday in a car crash 
at 109th Street and Crenshaw Boulevard in Inglewood, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The children, whose names were not released, were passengers in the same car 
when the mid-afternoon accident occurred, a police spokesman said. Details of 
the incident -- which may have involved a single car -- were still being 
investigated, the spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
