<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEST BET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE RAMOS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 22nd annual Long Beach Boat Show, launched by the Southern California 
Marine Assn., will bring a variety of boats and equipment displays to the Long 
Beach Convention and Entertainment Center beginning Friday and sailing through 
Oct. 28. The event traditionally assembles the largest fleet of show boats and 
boating accessories in the West, and is the time when many manufacturers 
introduce new models. 
</P>
<P>
Approximately 475 pleasure boats, both power and sail, from 125 brand-name boat 
lines, will be featured. More than 300 booths will display equipment, supplies 
and services for recreational boats. Booths will feature representatives and 
merchandise from sailmakers, spar builders, engine dealers, communications and 
navigational electronics, boat trailers, water skis and more. 
</P>
<P>
An educational feature at the boat show will be a panel of experts on 
long-distance cruising, sailboat racing, fishing and water skiing. They will 
take turns presenting a series of two seminars a night through Oct. 27. 
Included on the panel are Gerry Cunningham, columnist for Pacific Boating 
Almanac and Sea magazine; Bill Gaither, professional tournament fisherman and 
wildlife artist and writer; Earl Hinz, Pacific contributing editor for Cruising 
World magazine; Ronnie Kovach, professional fishing instructor; and Scott 
Gobel, a member of the Kidder professional ski team. 
</P>
<P>
There also will be a drawing at the end of the show for a seven-day vacation 
for two to Tahiti via Air New Zealand. 
</P>
<P>
The boat show will be open at the center, 300 E. Ocean Blvd., from 3 to 10 p.m. 
weekdays, 11 a.m. to 10 p.m. Saturdays, and 11 a.m. to 7 p.m. Sundays. Tickets 
are $5 for adults, children under 12 are free, and discount tickets are 
available from Southern California Marine Assn. members, marine retail stores 
and participating Kinko's Copy Centers. For more information, call the Southern 
California Marine Assn. at (714) 633-7581. MIKE RAMOS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
