<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: DICKERSON AGREES TO FOUR-YEAR EXTENSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eric Dickerson and the Indianapolis Colts patched up their differences Saturday 
and the running back signed a four-year contract extension. 
</P>
<P>
General Manager Jim Irsay said Dickerson will have a physical Monday and is 
scheduled to practice with the team Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson is expected to play against the Denver Broncos a week from today. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson, his attorney and advisers reached the agreement in a meeting with 
owner Robert Irsay, team attorney Michael Chernoff and Jim Irsay at the owner's 
home north of Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson, seventh on the NFL's all-time rushing list, has been on the Colts' 
reserve non-football injury list since the start of the season. He is eligible 
to be activated Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
No financial terms were announced. Dickerson had been scheduled to receive 
$1.45 million in 1990, the last year of his contract. However, he stands to 
lose more than $600,000 for the portion of the season he has missed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
