<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Azumah Nelson of Ghana used a left jab to keep Juan LaPorte at bay and retain 
the WBC super-featherweight title with a unanimous 12-round decision at Sydney, 
Australia. 
</P>
<P>
Nelson was pinned on the ropes four times by LaPorte, who had held the title 
from 1982-84. 
</P>
<P>
Nelson, who raised his record to 32-2, never hurt LaPorte, who seemed more 
annoyed that he couldn't get close enough to do any serious damage to the 
champion. Still, Nelson connected often enough to win, 116-112, 116-113 and 
115-113, on the three judges' cards. 
</P>
<P>
LaPorte, a 30-year-old, New York-based Puerto Rican whose record fell to 36-11, 
felt he had won. But he praised Nelson's successful tactics. 
</P>
