<HEADLINE>
<P>
'WESTSIDE REPORT' WINS CABLE TV NEWS AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Continental Cablevision's "Westside Report," a weekly half-hour newscast, has 
been awarded the Southern California Cable Assn.'s Diamond Award for Best Local 
News Program. 
</P>
<P>
Executive producer of "Westside Report" is Marcelo M. Cruz, news director is 
Glen Gaither, managing editor is Alec Murdock and director is Bruce Germain. 
</P>
<P>
The show airs Wednesdays at 8 p.m. on Continental Cablevision's Channel 37, and 
Fridays at 11:30 a.m. on Century Cable's Channel 3. Continental and Century 
serve nearly all of the Westside. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
