<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY SOLTIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
L.A. Southwest 22, Ventura 6 -- Southwest, coming off three consecutive losses, 
not only held visiting Ventura to six points but intercepted five passes, 
sacked the quarterback seven times, blocked two passes and recovered a fumble. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars were held to only 66 yards rushing and 214 yards overall, but made 
the most of their opportunities. 
</P>
<P>
Southwest scored first when David Mack intercepted quarterback Tim Albrent and 
returned the ball 57 yards for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars scored again after Mack intercepted his second pass. On the first 
play after the interception, quarterback Craig Manigo passed 45 yards to wide 
receiver Michael Stevens for a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Mack's third interception set up Southwest's last touchdown. From Ventura's 
35-yard line, Manigo pitched the ball to Jessie Wallace, who passed to a wide 
open Robert Avery. TONY SOLTIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
