<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Campaign funds -- A headline in Thursday's San Gabriel Valley section indicated 
that Diamond Bar City Councilman Paul Horcher, the Republican nominee in the 
52nd Assembly District, had raised substantially more campaign funds than his 
Democratic opponent because of loans he had made to himself. Actually, Horcher 
raised $104,998 without the loans, and his Democratic opponent, Gary Neely, 
raised $22,586. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the article should have stated that Horcher is paying consultant Harvey 
Englander $15,000 for his work since the June 5 primary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Correction 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
